You're talking about the border of just the textfield part, right?

The relevant forms.css rule is:

435 input[type="file"] > input[type="text"] {
436   border-color: inherit;
437   background-color: inherit;
438   color: inherit;
439   font-size: inherit;
440   letter-spacing: inherit;
441 }

So you're seeing it pick up just the border-color, but not the width or style, as expected....

I suppose we could inherit the border entirely.  David, thoughts?

